HTML Links:

✅ Basic Link Syntax:
<a href="https://www.example.com">Visit Example</a>

--href is the destination URL
--The text between <a> and </a> is the clickable part

✅ Open Link in a New Tab
<a href="https://www.google.com" target="_blank">Open Google in New Tab</a>

--target="_blank" makes the link open in a new tab

✅ Add Title (Optional Tooltip)
<a href="https://www.w3schools.com" title="Learn web development">Visit W3Schools</a>

Example Code:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>HTML Links</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Day 7: HTML Links</h1>

    <p>Here is a normal link:</p>
    <a href="https://www.example.com">Go to Example.com</a>

    <p>Here is a link that opens in a new tab:</p>
    <a href="https://www.google.com" target="_blank">Open Google</a>

    <p>Here is a link with a title tooltip:</p>
    <a href="https://www.w3schools.com" title="Great resource to learn HTML">Visit W3Schools</a>
  </body>
</html>
